Section 6: Dealing with Integration and Batch Processing
### Lecture 6.3: Batch data processing with Spring Batch

* Anatomy of Batch Job
              *
    Job -------------------->   Step
     |
     *
     |
     V
    Job Instance               step scope
     |
     *
     |
     V                *
    JobExecution   --------->  StepExecution
  * Spring Batch Job component
    * ItemReader
    * ItemProcessor (Optional)
    * ItemWriter

* Spring Boot and Batch
  * Spring Boot sets up DataSource, a TransactionManager and a
    TaskScheduler, turns on @EnableBatchProcessing
  * Launches all Jobs defined in the context at startup
  * Publishes ApplicationContextEvents related to Job runs